main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Modesto, California on March 25, 1955.
interesting points: The object was the size of a basketball held at arm's length.
The object was observed for approximately two hours.
The Modesto airport and the possibility of a local searchlight used for practice were considered as the probable cause of the sighting.
The conclusion was that the sighting was likely due to natural causes, balloons, aircraft, astronomical phenomena, or a hoax, with insufficient data for a full evaluation.
No further report was found in the file.
result: Insufficient data for evaluation, possibly natural or man-made causes.
sighted object: An object the size of a basketball held at arm's length
photographs: No photographs included in the report.
